article.headline: UALR 75, South Alabama 50
article.story: LITTLE ROCK, Ark. -- D'Andre Williams scored 14 points and Courtney Jackson added 12, combining to shoot 4 for 4 from 3-point distance, and Arkansas-Little Rock routed South Alabama 75-50 Thursday night. UALR (9-13, 6-2 Sun Belt) shot 3-pointers at a 45.5 percent clip and netted 13 of 15 free throws. South Alabama (10-9, 2-6) fell behind 18-7 within the game's first eight minutes and trailed 35-22 at halftime. UALR opened the second half on a 17-4 run to lead 52-26 at the 12:06 mark to ensure the lopsided victory. South Alabama's Augustine Rubit led all scorers with 22 points on 7 of 10 shooting to compliment his team-leading seven rebounds. South Alabama shot a paltry 25 percent (4 of 16) from 3-point range.
